<figureCitation id="135559FEF454FFA9FF5068BE5BA3FE2B" box="[136,244,410,436]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="11.[136,229,1211,1233]" captionTargetBox="[154,1421,464,1180]" captionTargetId="figure-111@11.[151,1436,458,1183]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 10. Puccinia thaliae Dietel on Canna indica (TA419). A Hypophyllous uredinia B urediniospores drawn in optical sections except one spore. Scale bar: 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597631/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">Figure 10</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF1115F3F454FFA9FF506D9F5AB7FB6A" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597631" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6597631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597631/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="138" startId="11.[136,229,1211,1233]" targetBox="[154,1421,464,1180]" targetPageId="11">
<paragraph id="8BD1457BF454FFA9FF506D9F5AB7FB6A" blockId="11.[136,1451,1211,1269]" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F454FFA9FF506D9F5A5BFB4F" bold="true" box="[136,268,1211,1233]" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">FIGURE 10.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F454FFA9FECB6D985AA1FB4E" authority="Dietel" authorityName="Dietel" box="[275,502,1211,1233]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="11" pageNumber="138" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="thaliae">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F454FFA9FECB6D985AE4FB4F" box="[275,435,1211,1233]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">Puccinia thaliae</emphasis>
Dietel
</taxonomicName>
on 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F454FFA9FDC66D9F59F6FB4F" box="[542,673,1211,1232]" class="Liliopsida" family="Cannaceae" genus="Canna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="11" pageNumber="138" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F454FFA9FDC66D9F59F6FB4F" box="[542,673,1211,1232]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">Canna indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(TA419). 
<emphasis id="B91A9969F454FFA9FCD16D9F584DFB4F" bold="true" box="[777,794,1211,1232]" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">A</emphasis>
Hypophyllous uredinia 
<emphasis id="B91A9969F454FFA9FBD16D9F5F4EFB4F" bold="true" box="[1033,1049,1211,1232]" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">B</emphasis>
urediniospores drawn in optical sections except one spore. Scale bar: 10 µm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BD1457BF454FFA9FF506C075F3EFA36" blockId="11.[136,1452,1315,2064]" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F454FFA9FF506C075BA6FAA2" bold="true" box="[136,241,1315,1341]" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">Uredinia</emphasis>
amphigenous, more abundant on the adaxial side, scattered, yellow orange, erumpent, subepidermal, associated with chlorotic yellow-orange spots, spots dark brown in severe infections. 
<emphasis id="B91A9969F454FFA9FB826C635E58FAFE" bold="true" box="[1114,1295,1351,1377]" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">Urediniospores</emphasis>
ellipsoidal to broadly ellipsoidal or pyriform, rarely globose, (27–)30–39(–45) × (15–)19–25(–28) µm (n = 30), pale yellow to hyaline, spore wall 2–3 µm thick, echinulate, germ pores not visible. 
<emphasis id="B91A9969F454FFA9FC486CAB589DFA36" bold="true" box="[912,970,1423,1449]" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">Telia</emphasis>
not observed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD1457BF454FFA9FF656C905FC5FA6D" blockId="11.[136,1452,1315,2064]" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">
A 28S rDNA sequence of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F454FFA9FE3C6C905919FA52" box="[484,590,1459,1485]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="11" pageNumber="138" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="thaliae">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F454FFA9FE3C6C905919FA52" box="[484,590,1459,1485]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">P. thaliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from a specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="F37905EBF454FFA9FC8F6C9758CDFA52" box="[855,922,1459,1485]" name="Benin" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">Benin</collectingCountry>
shares 100% (890/892) sequence identity with previously published sequences of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E3EF8F454FFA9FDC86CFC592EFA6E" box="[528,633,1495,1521]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="11" pageNumber="138" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="thaliae">
<emphasis id="B91A9969F454FFA9FDC86CFC592EFA6E" box="[528,633,1495,1521]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">P. thaliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g. 
<accessionNumber id="943DD898F454FFA9FD616CF35878FA6E" box="[697,815,1495,1521]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/JX206994" pageId="11" pageNumber="138">JX206994</accessionNumber>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF388AF454FFA9FCE26CF35FD1FA6D" author="Padamsee, M. &amp; McKenzie, E. H. C." box="[826,1158,1495,1522]" pageId="11" pageNumber="138" pagination="139 - 141" refId="ref13056" refString="Padamsee, M. &amp; McKenzie, E. H. C. (2012) First report of Puccinia thaliae on canna lily in New Zealand and in some Pacific island countries. Australasian Plant Disease Notes 7: 139 - 141. https: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / s 13314 - 012 - 0069 - 3" type="journal article" year="2012">Padamsee &amp; McKenzie 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
